### Test Anomaly Detection Engine
### Base URL: http://localhost:4000/api

### Detect anomaly for a single event
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "action": "write",
  "file": "/etc/config",
  "status": "denied"
}

### Get baseline for a specific user
GET http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/baselines/testuser

### Get all user baselines
GET http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/all-baselines

### Reset baseline for specific user
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/reset/testuser
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Reset all baselines
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/reset-all
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Full event pipeline with anomaly detection
POST http://localhost:4000/api/events/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "raw_event": "{\"username\":\"newuser\",\"action\":\"delete\",\"file\":\"/etc/shadow\",\"status\":\"denied\"}"
}

### Process sequence to see anomaly scores evolve
### 1st event - NEW_USER signal triggers (0.60 anomaly score)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "action": "read"
}

### 2nd event - same user, same action (baseline established)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "action": "read"
}

### 3rd event - RARE_ACTION signal triggers (0.40 anomaly score)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "action": "delete"
}

### 4th event - BURST signal triggers (0.30 anomaly score) within 2 seconds
POST http://localhost:4000/api/anomaly/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "action": "write"
}

### Notes:
# - New User Score: 0.60 - triggers on first event for any user
# - Rare Action Score: 0.40 - triggers when action < 10% of user's events (after 5+ events)
# - Burst Score: 0.30 - triggers when 2+ events within 2 seconds
# - Multiple signals can stack (e.g., NEW_USER + BURST = 0.90)
# - Anomaly scores are capped at 1.0
# - Baselines persist in-memory; reset on server restart (use Redis for persistence)
